<HEAD>Front Spreads Rain Over Great Lakes, Leaves Freeze in Its Wake</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   A cold front spread showers and thunderstorms across the Great
Lakes region and left near-freezing temperatures in its wake in the
northern Plains early today.
   Cold Canadian air poured into the north-central part of the
country, dropping temperatures below the freezing mark along the
border and leaving readings in the 30s elsewhere in Minnesota, the
Dakotas, parts of Michigan, Wisconsin, Nebraska and Iowa.
   Temperatures also were in the 30s across part of the northern
Rockies.
   Thunderstorms were reported Monday evening in the lower Great
Lakes and northern parts of the upper Ohio Valley. Cloud cover
spread from the Great Lakes to much of the northern Atlantic Coast.
   Showers and thunderstorms also developed over much of Arizona on
Monday.
   Today's forecast called for sunshine and highs in the 60s and
70s in much of the nation. Showers were predicted in the central
and northern Appalachians and the eastern Great Lakes and
thunderstorms were expected in Arizona and southern portions of
Nevada and Utah. Snow was forecast for northern Michigan.
   Highs were expected to be in the 40s and 50s from the Great
Lakes region to the northern and central Appalachians; in 80s in
southern portions of Florida and Texas, and from central Montana to
much of Oregon and Washington; and in the 80s to mid-90s in the
desert Southwest.
   At 3 a.m. EDT, temperatures ranged from 27 degrees at Warroad,
Minn., to 84 degrees at Yuma, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 52 fair; Boston 54 cloudy; Buffalo 45 showers;
Charleston, S.C. 54 fair; Cincinnati 43 fair; Cleveland 50 partly
cloudy; Detroit 43 fair; Miami 72 fair; New York 59 cloudy;
Philadelphia 57 partly cloudy; Pittsburgh 44 fair; Portland, Maine
53 cloudy; Washington 57 cloudy.
   _Central: Bismarck 32 fair; Chicago 48 windy; Dallas-Fort Worth
56 fair; Denver 45 fair; Des Moines 43 fair; Indianapolis 43 fair;
Kansas City 49 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 43 fair; Nashville 56
fair; New Orleans 59 fair; St. Louis 53 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 46 fair; Anchorage 33 cloudy; Las Vegas 68
fair; Los Angeles 65 fair; Phoenix 73 fair; Salt Lake City 50 fair;
San Diego 63 foggy; San Francisco 56 foggy; Seattle 54 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 54 showers; Toronto 45 partly cloudy.
