<HEAD>Laughter The Best Defense Against Ungrammatical Robber</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WINDSOR, Va. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The sheriff does not recommend it as a
standard defense against robbery, but laughter was the undoing of a
would-be bad man.
   An unidentified man entered Red's Supermarket on Sunday
afternoon and gave the clerk a note reading, ``This a holdup.''
   The busted syntax was too much for the clerk, who broke up in
laughter, said Isle of Wight County Sheriff Charles Phelps.
Likewise, the laughter was too much for the suspected robber, who
fled the store after taking a 69-cent package of cigars.
   While laughter turned aside this robber, ``I don't recommend
that to everybody,'' said Phelps.
   Police are still searching for the suspect.
</TEXT>
