<1ST_LINE>r i PM-Obit-Percy     10-11 0166</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Obit-Percy,0169</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Hugh Algernon Percy, 10th Duke of Northumberland, Dies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Hugh Algernon Percy, the 10th duke of
Northumberland and a descendant of one of Britain's leading
families of nobility, died today, a family spokeswoman said. He was
74.
   The duke died of a suspected heart attack at his London
residence, said the spokeswoman at his ancestral home of Alnwick
Castle in the northern England county of Northumberland. She spoke
on condition of anonymity.
   He was descended from the first earl of Northumberland, Sir
Henry Percy, who won fame for his zeal in border warfare against
the Scottish in the late 14th century. The dukedom was created in
1766.
   Hugh Algernon Percy is succeeded by his eldest son, Henry Alan
Walter Richard Percy, 35. The duke is survived by his wife,
Elizabeth Diana Montagu-Douglas-Scott, two other sons and three
daughters.
   A private funeral will be held later this week, the family
spokeswoman said, followed by memorial services at Alnwick Castle
and Westminster Abbey.
</TEXT>
