<1ST_LINE>r i AM-BRF--CrimeKilling     10-11 0158</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Crime Killing,0162</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Crime Boss Killed in Barber Shop While Getting Shave</HEAD>
<DATELINE>REGGIO CALABRIA, Italy (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A gunman killed a local crime boss
in a barber shop Tuesday, pumping seven bullets into him as he sat
for a shave, police said.
   The gunman and a lookout, both wearing helmets that covered
their faces, sped away on a high-powered motorcycle, witnesses said.
   Killed was Demetrio Serraino, 48, described as a boss of the
'ndrangheta, the Mafia-like crime syndicate in Calabria, the region
in the toe of the Italian boot.
   Serraino, who had an arrest record for criminal association and
extortion, died en route to a hospital, police said. The barber was
unhurt.
   The Italian news agency ANSA said the killing was the 42nd
homicide in the city of Reggio Calabria this year, many of them
linked to a war between rival criminal gangs.
   A cousin of Serraino was killed in 1986 in his hospital room by
gunmen.
</TEXT>
