<2ND_LINE>AM-Kenya-Bandits,0129</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Bandits Attack Truck; 10 Killed</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NAIROBI, Kenya (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Gun-wielding bandits ambushed a truck
carrying people home from market day in Kenya's arid north, killing
10 of the 20 people aboard and wounding the other 10, the police
commissioner said Tuesday.
   The assailants fired from the roadside bush late Monday near
Rapsu, about 140 miles north of Nairobi, said Commissioner Philip
Kilonzo.
   Two of those killed were police officers who were returning with
the other passengers from Kina, a local trading town, to Rapsu,
according to the Daily Nation. The bandits escaped with a rifle and
120 rounds of ammunition, the newspaper said.
   The attack took place in the same district where bandits
massacred 15 villagers at their homes by bandits in April.
</TEXT>
