<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Zimbabwe,0123</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Law Professors Protest Expulsion of Kenyan</HEAD>
<DATELINE>HARARE, Zimbabwe (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Members of the law faculty at the
University of Zimbabwe on Tuesday protested the deportation of a
Kenyan colleague for his alleged links to recent student
demonstrations.
   Shadrack Gutto, who was given 48 hours by immigration
authorities to leave Zimbabwe, flew to London on Friday.
   No official reasons were given for the expulsion of Gutto, who
allegedly fanned campus unrest against government corruption that
earlier this month led to the bloodiest riots in Zimbabwe since it
won independence from Britain in 1980.
   The 11 law professors said they filed a protest with the
government and have requested to discuss the deportation with
President Robert Mugabe.
</TEXT>
