<HEAD>Vietnam Frees 160 Thai Fishermen</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A group of 160 Thai fishermen arrested
for poaching in Vietnamese waters returned home Tuesday after
Thailand paid $1,000 each for their release.
   The fishermen, who were arrested in the fall of 1987, arrived in
Bangkok on a flight from Ho Chi Minh City.
   Seventy-three other Thai fishermen held by Vietnam since last
fall also are to return home Friday.
