<1ST_LINE>d a AM-BRF--TV-USAToday 1stLd-Writethru a0629 10-11 0186</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--TV-USA Today, 1st Ld - Writethru, a0629,0183</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>`USA Today: The Television Show' Hires Managing Editor</HEAD>
<NOTE>Eds: Drops `new' in first graf to indicate there was no previous
managing editor.</NOTE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   ``USA Today: The Television Show,'' which
premiered last month to criticism that it has too much style and
not enough content, has hired a managing editor.
   Jim Bellows, a former editor of the Los Angeles Herald Examiner,
served as executive editor of ABC's ``World News Tonight'' after a
1981-1983 stint as managing editor of ``Entertainment Tonight.''
For the past two years, he has been an executive with Prodigy, a
home computer information service.
   Grant Tinker, president of GTG Entertainment, his joint
production venture with Gannett, the publisher of USA Today, the
newspaper, called Bellows ``exactly the right person'' to oversee
the content of the nationally syndicated newsmagazine.
   Despite rumors that the show would be dropped because of
disappointing ratings, Tinker said the addition of Bellows along
with recent format changes give him ``every confidence that `USA
Today: The Television Show' is well on its way to a long and happy
future.''
</TEXT>
