<1ST_LINE>r i AM-Britain-Nuclear     10-11 0173</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Britain-Nuclear,0178</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Lab At Nuclear Plant Contaminated With Plutonium</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A laboratory inside a nuclear complex in
northwestern England has been contaminated with plutonium, the
plant's operator said Tuesday.
   Above-normal traces of radioactivity were detected Monday on the
floor of an analytical laboratory handling plutonium at the
Sellafield nuclear plant and in a small area of the corridor
outside, said a spokesman for British Nuclear Fuels Ltd. who
requested anonymity.
   No workers at the plant, about 260 miles northwest of London in
Cumbria, have been exposed to dangerous levels of radioactivity nor
has there been a release into the environment, the spokesman said.
   The Sellafield complex is the world's largest nuclear
reprocessing center, extracting uranium and plutonium from spent
nuclear fuel used by reactors in Britain and other countries.
   The Irish government and environmental groups have repeatedly
criticized the plant's discharge of radioactive waste into the
Irish Sea as a health hazard and have demanded the plant's closure.
   The company says its discharges and leaks have been within safe
limits.
</TEXT>
