<HEAD>Eugene McCarthy Files As Presidential Write-In For Arizona</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PHOENIX, Ariz. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Backers of Eugene McCarthy's independent
campaign for president filed papers Tuesday to certify him as a
write-in candidate in Arizona.
   Arizona coordinator Stockton Wingo said McCarthy is on the
ballot in only four or five states but he has qualified as a
write-in in another 15 states or so and plans to make the filing
deadlines in additional states.
   McCarthy, a former U.S. senator from Minnesota, first came to
national prominence in 1968 when his opposition to the Vietnam war
and his Democratic Party candidacy for president helped drive
then-President Lyndon Johnson from the race.
   Johnson's vice president, Hubert Humphrey, beat McCarthy for the
nomination at a riot-torn national convention in Chicago but lost
the election to Republican Richard Nixon.
 
</TEXT>
