<DOCNO> AP881011-0234 </DOCNO>
<FILEID>AP-NR-10-11-88 0023EDT</FILEID>
<1ST_LINE>r f PM-Forbes-Careers     10-11 0110</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Forbes-Careers,0115</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Real Estate Is Top Source of Wealth for Forbes 400</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   In a throwback to the days of the landed gentry,
real estate has become the No. 1 source of wealth for members of
the Forbes 400 wealthiest Americans.
   Eighty-seven of the Forbes 400 made their fortunes principally
from real estate, up from 73 last year, Forbes says.
   Following real estate, manufacturing accounted for 75 of the
Forbes 400 fortunes, media enterprises for 73, financial operations
for 65, oil and gas for 30, retailing for 21, agriculture for 16
and high technology for 15. A variety of sources accounted for the
18 other fortunes.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
