<1ST_LINE>r f BC-Earns-Westinghouse     10-11 0198</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Earns-Westinghouse,0205</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Westinghouse Reports Third-Quarter Profits</HEAD>
<DATELINE>PITTSBURGH (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Westinghouse Electric Corp. on Tuesday
reported its profit rose 13.3 percent in the third quarter on a 10
percent increase in revenues.
   The company said net income rose to $204.6 million, or $1.41 per
common share, compared with $180.6 million, or $1.25 a share, in
the 1987 third quarter. Revenue during the quarter ended Sept. 30
totaled $3.06 billion, up from $2.77 billion a year ago.
   Westinghouse Chairman John C. Marous said the company's
industries segment had significantly higher revenues. He also
reported higher revenues for the financial services, broadcasting
and electronic systems segments.
   However, revenues for its energy and utility systems and
commercial segments were down for the third quarter.
   ``Order activity remained strong,'' Marous said. ``We are
meeting our sales and earnings targets, and we expect that 1988
will be another good year of growth and improvements in
operations.''
   For the first nine months, the company reported profits of
$574.1 million, or $3.95 per common share, on revenues of $8.85
billion, up 13.7 percent from profits of $505 million, or $3.51 per
common share, on revenues of $8.04 billion in the first nine months
of 1987.
