<1ST_LINE>r f BC-AutoRecalls     10-11 0168</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Recalls,0175</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Ford Recalls 167,000 Trucks for Electrical, Glass Problems</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ford Motor Co. recalled about 167,000
minivans and trucks Tuesday because of possible problems in wiring
under front seats and in rear window glass.
   One of the two recalls involves about 103,000 1986 Aerostar,
Bronco II and Ranger SuperCab vehicles. The company said some
wiring under front seats may become pinched or worn, cause a short
circuit and ignite seat cushions.
   Dealers will install a new fuse and the wiring will be moved at
no charge to owners.
   In the other recall, Ford said some optional, sliding rear
windows may be defective in about 64,000 1988 model F-150, F250 and
F-350 trucks.
   Ford said the glass may not have been tempered properly and
could break into pieces larger than allowed by federal law.
Defective windows would be replaced at no charge to the owner.
   Ford spokesman Mike Parris said the company was aware of no
injuries stemming from either of the problems.
</TEXT>
