<2ND_LINE>BC-Goodrich Sale,0137</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>BFGoodrich Negotiating To Sell Aircraft Tire Operations</HEAD>
<DATELINE>AKRON, Ohio (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Michelin and the BFGoodrich Co. announced
Tuesday that they were negotiating the sale of BFGoodrich's
aircraft tire operation to Michelin.
   BFGoodrich makes brakes and wheels for military and civil
aircraft. The company's aircraft tire operations include a Norwood,
N.C., factory, retread operations in the United States and Canada,
and marketing, sales, research, and testing operations.
   David Burner, president of Goodrich's aerospace division, said,
``The manufacture of aircraft tires no longer fits our strategy for
our growing aerospace division. We are pleased that a company with
as strong a commitment and resources as Michelin has will continue
to operate this business.''
   Final sale of the aircraft tire operation is contingent on
approval from government agencies, the companies said.
</TEXT>
