<2ND_LINE>BC-Auto Incentives,0184</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>GM Divisions Announce Incentives</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DETROIT (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   General Motors Corp. on Tuesday announced cash
buyer incentives and rebates effective immediately for a variety of
Chevrolet, Pontiac, Buick and GMC trucks and cars.
   A $750 cash incentive program for the Chevrolet Caprice will
expire Dec. 25, 1988, and incentives on a variety of Chevrolet
pickup and other light-duty trucks, ranging from $300 to $500, will
end Nov. 30.
   Incentives for some Pontiac cars will range from $350 to $600
and will remain in effect until Jan. 3, 1989.
   Rebates between $300 and $500 will be in effect for several GMC
pickup and sport utility vehicles through Nov. 30.
   Buick is offering through Dec. 31 rebates of $750 on 1988
Electra-Park Avenues and Regals. The money can be used as part of a
down payment. Regal buyers also may choose to receive interest
rates ranging from 3.9 percent for contracts up to 24 months to 9.9
percent for 60 months.
   Buick also is offering $500 rebates on 1989 Centurys and $300
rebates on 1989 Skylarks.
